column1: Table 2.38: Method of birth, by maternal age, 2021

(a) For NSW and the NT, ‘Non-instrumental vaginal’ includes all women who had a vaginal breech birth, whether or not instruments were used. For the remaining jurisdictions, ‘Non-instrumental vaginal’ includes vaginal breech births only where instruments were not used.
Note:For multiple births, the method of birth of the first-born baby was used.
Source: AIHW analysis of National Perinatal Data Collection.
